Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Drain and slice the @smoked tofu{225%g} into 2 two
slices per person and lay them on some #kitchen paper{}. Lay some more kitchen
paper on top and leave to the side.

> This is to dry the tofu.

Meanwhile, trim the ends from the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and thinly sliced) and
thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
Mix the @miso paste{15%g} with half the @honey{30%g} in a #small bowl{}.

Put the @rice vinegar{15%g} into a #large bowl{} with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and a
@salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Mix, then add the cucumber, toss to coat
in the vinegar. Set aside.

Put the @cornflour{20%g} on a #plate{}, add a @salt{large pinch}, stir well.
Discard the kitchen paper then drizzle the tofu slices with @oil{}. Once nicely
coated, press both sides into the cornflour until evenly covered.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #large saucepan{} and bring to the
boil. When boiling, add a @salt{pinch}, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, lower
the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for
~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to
the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Once you have turned the tofu over, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. Add the @sliced mushrooms{150%g}. Stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the @soy sauce{12.5%g}, remaining honey and half the
garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover with #foil{}. Pop
your pan back on the heat, add another drizzle of @oil{}, the
@sliced spring greens{150%g} and a @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.
Stir-fry until they are tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add the remaining garlic, cook
for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir half the coriander through the spring greens. Fluff up the rice with a
#fork{} and spoon onto one side of your bowls. Arrange the cucumber pickle,
spring greens and teriyaki mushrooms alongside and lay the tofu on top. Sprinkle
over the remaining coriander and @sesame seeds{15%g}. Enjoy!